DPRK Full of Confidence in Victory 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 4 (KCNA) -- All the people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have greeted the New Year Juche 96(2007) full of confidence in victory.
 They, with great optimism, are all out in response to the dynamic call "Usher in a great heyday of Songun Korea full of confidence in victory!" set forth in the joint New Year editorial of Rodong Sinmun, Joson Inmingun and Chongnyon Jonwi.
 Last year they keenly experienced that the army and people of the DPRK were entirely right when they had invariably followed the road of Songun over the past 10-odd years in the face of the severest trials and came to have a firm belief that they can certainly build a great, prosperous and powerful nation in near future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, the Korean people have augmented the strength of the nation remarkably and secured a springboard for a fresh leap forward in all sectors of the socialist economic construction. They are effecting miracles and innovations every day with a resolution to make a signal success in the offensive campaign for building an economic power this year again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Surging are the enthusiasm of officials and working people in the people's committees of all levels and the fields of light industry and public service who are positively responding to the call of the Party for directing the primary effort to improving the standard of the people's living as the main task in the present general march.
 The editorial says that the people should, as in the past, keep up farming as the great foundation of the country and make an epoch-making advance in solving the problem of food for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In response to the call, the agricultural workers, with a firm determination to increase the grain production this year, are striving hard to acquire new arable land and raise the fertility of soil while energetically carrying on the water-way project of Miru Plain to be converted into a granary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With responsibility for a pilot of the national economy, the workers in the field of the electric power industry including the Pyongyang Thermal-power Complex are brilliantly carrying out their daily assignments from the beginning of the year.
 The workers of the Musan Mine Complex, who had succeeded in blasting 100,000 cubic meters of earth on the first day of the year to make a breakthrough in turning out large quantities of concentrated iron ore, are making every effort to hit the production target for the first month of the year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Labor achievements have been reported from the Songjin Steel Complex, the Ryongsong Machinery Complex and other industrial establishments.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Glorifying This Year with Proud Victories and Feats 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Thursday in an editorial calls for glorifying with proud victories and feats the significant year of 2007, in which the Korean people will commemorate the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung and the 75th anniversary of the foundation of the Korean People's Army.
 Noting that the army and people of the DPRK are speeding up the grand march to glorify this auspicious year, full of great pride and self-confidence of being victors in warm response to the joint New Year editorial, Rodong Sinmun says: 
 It is necessary to bring about a revolutionary turn in the economic construction and the efforts to improve the standard of the people's living with the might of invincible Songun politics and single-minded unity of the whole Party, the entire army and all the people around the headquarters of the revolution this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole Party, the entire army and all the people should turn out in the drive to bring about a fresh revolutionary surge by the force of Songun and thus glorify the significant year of 2007 as a year of great prosperity unprecedented in the history of the Party and the country. This is the most important task devolved upon the Korean people at present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should vigorously accelerate the general march for Songun revolution, holding aloft the slogan "Usher in a great heyday of Songun Korea full of confidence in victory!"
 We should accomplish the cause of building a powerful and prosperous country pioneered by the President, keeping deep in our minds that our leader, our ideology and our system are best. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should fully demonstrate the political and ideological might of our revolutionary ranks in which all the army and people are single-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should more vigorously bring about a great Songun revolutionary upswing on all fronts for the building of an economic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should make another leap forward and innovation startling the world in the on-going worthwhile march to bring an era of prosperity to Songun Korea with the same persevering will with which we brought about the dawn of victory, overcoming grave ordeals and difficulties.

Ushering in Heyday of Cause of Independent Reunification Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Thursday calls for adding brilliance to the June 15 era of reunification by forcefully accelerating the march toward independent reunification this year. 
 The author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Add brilliance to the June 15 reunification era by attaching importance to the nation, maintaining peace and achieving unity!" This is the slogan which the whole nation should uphold this year. It clearly indicates the fighting tasks the Korean nation should carry out in the new year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "By our nation itself", the spirit of the June 15 era of reunification, is the most steadfast idea of attaching importance to the nation. The Korean nation should regard it as the strict rule to develop the inter-Korean relations and the reunification movement according to the idea of "By our nation itself". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle to safeguard peace is a just patriotic struggle for defending the existence of the nation and its land of living. All the fellow countrymen should turn out as one man in the struggle to defend peace with death-defying will, staking the destiny of the cause of independent reunification and the security of the nation. 
 All the Koreans in the north, the south and overseas should intensify the struggle to consolidate the achievements made in the patriotic movement for the great unity of the nation last year and boost the unity of the entire nation.  This year, too, they should bring the atmosphere of national reconciliation and unity to a high tide and push it to independent reunification. It is important to wage a relentless struggle against the south Korean conservative forces standing in the way of national unity.
 It is an entirely just and realistic patriotic initiative that the joint editorial put forward the three major tasks to attach importance to the nation, defend peace and achieve unity which the Korean nation should carry through in the new year. If these three tasks are fulfilled to the letter, a brighter prospect will spread in accomplishing the cause of peace and independent reunification this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans should firmly defend and invariably implement the north-south joint declaration, whatever ordeals and difficulties they may face, thus adding shine to the June 15 era of reunification.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates an article to the 15th anniversary of the publication of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's work "The Historical Lesson in Building Socialism and the General Line of Our Party."
 This work gives a scientific exposition of the main cause of the collapse of socialism in some countries and indicates a clear road to the victory of socialism, the author of the article says, and goes on:
 The 15 years following the publication of the work were days when the sagacity of Kim Jong Il's leadership in guiding the cause of socialism to victory under the banner of Juche has been strikingly demonstrated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The leadership exploits performed by him in setting a brilliant example of building socialism under the banner of Songun find manifestation, above all, in that he provided an ideological and theoretical guideline for the victorious advance of socialism.
 On the basis of the unique revolutionary principle that the army is the party, the state and the people, he set forth the Songun revolutionary line and clearly expounded the strategy and tactics of the revolution in the Songun era, thus making it possible for the army and people of the DPRK to victoriously advance the cause of socialism based on a scientific revolutionary idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal exploits performed by him in setting an example for the era in building socialism lie also in that he unfolded a new history of the reinforcement of the driving force of the revolution with the revolutionary army as its main force.
 The most revolutionary, militant and mighty group in our society is the People's Army and its might will be remarkably augmented when unity in ideology and unity in fighting morale between the army and the people are achieved with the army as the main force of the revolution. This is the truth found by Kim Jong Il in the rugged path of revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The undying feats performed by him in creating the paragon of socialist construction for the era lies also in that he defended with honor the sovereignty and dignity of the country by resolutely upholding the revolutionary principle and class stand in the raging storm of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il who has firmly maintained the revolutionary principle and the class stand with faith and will of sure victory, the DPRK has become to display its dignity as a military power which no enemy dare provoke and a powerful independent state carrying on the revolution and construction its own way in conformity with the demand and interests of the people.

Pyongyangites Meet to Vow to Implement Tasks of  Joint New Year Editorial 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 4 (KCNA) -- A mass rally of Pyongyangites was held at Kim Il Sung Square Thursday to vow to bring about a fresh turn in building a great prosperous and powerful nation by dynamically pushing forward the Songun revolution in warm response to the joint editorial this year.
 The rally was attended by Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Ki Nam, Vice-Premiers Kwak Pom Gi and Ro Tu Chol, Cabinet members, leading officials of ministries, national institutions and working people's organizations, officials of the party and power organs, economic institutions and working people's organizations in the city, labor heroes, labor innovators and working people in the city.
 Pang Chol Gap, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, in a report said that the joint New Year editorial serves as a militant banner encouraging the entire party and army and all the people to make a dynamic general advance to attain the high goal of building a great prosperous and powerful nation by dynamically pushing forward the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people's access to nukes last year brought about a turning phase in building a great prosperous and powerful nation and resulted in such shining successes as demonstrating the resourcefulness and advantages of the Korean nation, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gaining great confidence from the dawn of victory ushered in by the Party, the officials and other working people in the city waged a heroic struggle to make a fresh leap forward in reinforcing the political and ideological position in the capital and economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Achievements were made in the agricultural production and the technological updating of the industrial establishments was accelerated to reinforce the economic foundation of the capital city. Not a few successes were made in the work to turn Pyongyang into a more magnificent city and a city of bliss. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called on all the citizens to usher in an era of prosperity in all fields in the country and dynamically wage an offensive to build a socialist economic power this year.
 Underscoring the need for the agricultural field to hold fast to the Party's policy to make a revolution in agriculture, he called on all fields to provide materials needed for farming on a priority basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also underlined the need to update the light industry factories, keep production going at a high rate, increase the variety of consumer goods and improve their quality and thus boost the supply of better consumer goods to people.
 He called for making production centers and catering network for improving the people's living standard pay off more profusely, improving the supply of commodities and service for the people and implementing the Party's health policy to enable the citizens to greatly benefit from the socialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials and other working people in the field of power and coal industries in the city should drastically increase production and those in the field of construction step up the construction of public buildings and dwelling houses and renovation and repair projects in main streets, make buildings formative and artistic and significantly improve the city management and, at the same time, continue dynamically pushing forward the work to turn rural villages into a socialist fairyland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for implementing to the letter the Party's line of attaching importance to science and technology to closely combine production with science and technology and produce a greater number of able intellectuals through education and stage a widespread campaign to raise the level of knowledge among the officials and other working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the rally.
 The speakers vowed to dynamically step up the technological updating of production processes and equipment, widely introduce valuable technical renovation proposals to production to bring about a great improvement in the production of consumer goods through the intensified revolution in the light industry. They also called for widely introducing high-yielding crops and domestic animals of good stock and scientific and advanced farming methods and successfully  doing double cropping to boost the per hectare yield of crops as required by the WPK's policy on the agricultural revolution.
 They called on the young citizens to volunteer to work at labor-consuming sectors of the socialist construction and fully display their energies and wisdom at major worksites to build a great prosperous and powerful nation including agricultural front and important construction sites just as their preceding generation of the revolution did.
 A resolution was adopted at the rally.

Rare Birds Fly in Migrant Reserve 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 4 (KCNA) -- More and more rare birds inhabit the Mundok Migrant Reserve on the western coast of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 There is a vast tideland on the low River Chongchon flowing into the West Sea of Korea. 
 According to the data available, there live more than 180 species of birds with over 150 species of migrants of them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of birds is approximately 50,000 and increases considerably year by year.
 World-wide efforts have been made to protect ecological system in swampy lands as an important link for biodiversity and international cooperation and exchange for it intensified. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Already from 10-odd years ago, the DPRK government has set the area with rich biodiversity for its natural and geographical features as a migrant reserve and paid a deep attention to its management. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several plans for protection and management of the reserve have been worked out so far and a biodiversity survey system was developed and used. 
 And relevant agencies have conducted varied activities in close contact with different international environmental protection organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Inhabiting there are such rare birds as black-faced spoonbill, Manchurian crane, white-fronted goose, white stork and spoon-billed sandpiper which are threatened with extinction around the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mundok Migrant Reserve is located on the route of seasonal birds.

Samurais' War Hysteria under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 4 (KCNA) -- The director general of the Japan Defence Agency and other samurais were recently reported to have provoked the DPRK by crying out for military sanctions against it. This comes under fire by a signed commentary of Rodong Sinmun Thursday.
 It is not only an intolerable insult to the DPRK but an undisguised war outcry that the group of militarists of this island country dared compare the DPRK with Japan before the World War II, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lurking behind this diatribe is their sinister intention to impose international blockade upon the DPRK and, furthermore, use force against it by labeling it a "dangerous state." This is clearly evidenced by the fact that the ruling quarters and the gentry of the Liberal Democratic Party of the island country called for stepping up the preparations for its participation in the above-said military sanctions.
 The DPRK has already clarified that it would regard any sanctions against it as a war declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The Japanese militarists' talk about military sanctions against the DPRK is intended to seize it through preemptive strikes as they precisely mean military attacks on it. This reflects the nature of the samurais who have grown corpulent through aggression, war and plunder and are keen to get richer by the same method in the future, too. 
 The above-said militarists are leaving no means untried to revenge the defeat suffered by the Japanese imperialists in the past, far from drawing a lesson from it.
 They have watched for a chance to stage a comeback to Korea for several decades since the end of the war, whetting their swords. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is one of the reasons why the ruling quarters in the land of Japs have deliberately deteriorated the DPRK-Japan relations, persistently raising the "abduction issue" which had already found its settlement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The aggressive nature and ambition of the Japanese militarists remain unchanged and their moves for reinvasion of Korea are getting more frantic as the days go by.
 Should the Japanese militarists dare preempt invasion of the DPRK to put it under their control, its army and people will deal merciless blows at them by the force of Songun and vent the towering grudge of the Korean people against their sworn enemy.
